        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2704149204" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10473654237324186301">I have to give this book at least a little credit for trying to relax a person living in a chaotic world. <br/><br/>It encourages one to stop and breathe for a moment, to enjoy sensations, flavors, and the beauty that exists around us. Enjoying small pleasures can definitely bring us brief moments of peace.<br/><br/>But that is where my compliments end. The rest of the book is pure rubbish. Self-worship is a better description of what this book teaches. While we are ultimately responsible for our own happiness, our</span>
  <span id="freeText10473654237324186301" style="display:none">I have to give this book at least a little credit for trying to relax a person living in a chaotic world. <br /><br />It encourages one to stop and breathe for a moment, to enjoy sensations, flavors, and the beauty that exists around us. Enjoying small pleasures can definitely bring us brief moments of peace.<br /><br />But that is where my compliments end. The rest of the book is pure rubbish. Self-worship is a better description of what this book teaches. While we are ultimately responsible for our own happiness, our happiness is not 'the meaning of life.' Happiness is a just result of a life well-lived. The author gets it backwards. If you're not living a meaningful life (other-centered and God-centered), you will NEVER find happiness by being self-centered.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10473654237324186301" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
